sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    actor U as User
    participant F as Frontend
    participant A as Auth Service
    participant D as PostgreSQL
    participant C as Redis Cache
    participant M as MongoDB Audit
    participant K as Kafka
    participant G as Google Authenticator

    Note over U,K: 1. Register — POST /auth/register

    U->>F: Fill register form
    F->>A: POST /auth/register {fullName, email, password}
    A->>A: RegisterPolicy.validateFullName / validateEmail / validatePassword

    alt Validation failed
        A-->>F: 400 {error: {message, code}}
        F-->>U: Show validation error
    else Validation passed
        A->>D: findByEmail(email)
        D-->>A: User | null

        alt Email already exists
            A->>M: create {action:REGISTER, status:FAILED, reason:EMAIL_ALREADY_EXISTS}
            A-->>F: 409 {error: {message: Email already exists, code: EMAIL_ALREADY_EXISTS}}
            F-->>U: Show error
        else Email available
            A->>A: bcrypt.hash(password, saltRounds=10)
            A->>A: role = adminEmails.includes(email) ? admin : user
            A->>A: id = uuidv4()
            A->>D: INSERT users {id, fullName, email, passwordHash, role}
            D-->>A: User created
            A->>M: create {action:REGISTER, status:SUCCESS, userId, email, role}
            A->>K: publish user.registered {userId, fullName, email, createdAt}
            A-->>F: 201 {id, fullName, email, role, isTwoFactorEnabled: false}
            F-->>U: Account created
        end
    end

    Note over U,K: 2. Login — POST /auth/login

    U->>F: Fill login form
    F->>A: POST /auth/login {email, password}
    A->>A: LoginPolicy.validateEmail / validatePassword
    A->>D: findByEmail(email)
    D-->>A: User | null

    alt User not found or password wrong
        A-->>F: 401 {error: {message: Invalid credentials, code: INVALID_CREDENTIALS}}
        F-->>U: Show error
    else Valid credentials — 2FA disabled
        A->>A: jwt.sign({userId, email, role}, JWT_ACCESS_SECRET, 15m) → accessToken
        A->>A: jwt.sign({userId, email, role}, JWT_REFRESH_SECRET, 7d) → refreshToken
        A->>M: create {action:LOGIN, status:SUCCESS, metadata:{viaTwoFactor:false}}
        A->>K: publish user.logged_in {userId, email, loggedInAt, viaTwoFactor: false}
        A-->>F: 200 {status:SUCCESS, accessToken} + Set-Cookie: refreshToken HttpOnly Secure SameSite=Strict
        F-->>U: Enter dashboard
    else Valid credentials — 2FA enabled
        A->>A: challengeId = uuidv4()
        A->>C: SET auth:login:challenge:{challengeId} = JSON.stringify({challengeId,userId,email,role,createdAt}) TTL:300s
        C-->>A: OK
        A-->>F: 202 {status:REQUIRE_2FA, challengeId, userId, email, message}
        F-->>U: Show 2FA code input
    end

    Note over U,C: 3. Start 2FA setup — POST /auth/2fa/init

    U->>F: Open 2FA setup page
    F->>A: POST /auth/2fa/init  Authorization: Bearer accessToken
    A->>A: requireAuth — jwt.verify(token, JWT_ACCESS_SECRET)
    A->>C: GET auth:blacklist:{accessToken}

    alt Token invalid or blacklisted
        A-->>F: 401 {error: {code: UNAUTHORIZED | TOKEN_INVALIDATED}}
        F-->>U: Redirect to login
    else Authenticated — userId from token payload
        A->>D: findById(userId)
        D-->>A: User found

        alt isTwoFactorEnabled already true
            A-->>F: 400 {error: {code: TWO_FACTOR_ALREADY_ENABLED}}
            F-->>U: Show already enabled message
        else Not yet enabled
            A->>A: speakeasy.generateSecret({label:email, issuer:Authentication Service})
            A->>A: qrcode.toDataURL(otpauthUrl) → qrCodeDataUrl
            A->>A: setupToken = uuidv4()
            A->>C: SET auth:2fa:setup:{userId}:{setupToken} = base32secret TTL:300s
            C-->>A: OK
            A->>M: create {action:ENABLE_2FA_INIT, status:INFO, userId, email, metadata:{setupToken}}
            A-->>F: 200 {qrCodeDataUrl, manualEntryKey, setupToken}
            F-->>U: Display QR code and manual entry key
        end
    end

    Note over U,G: 4. User adds account in Google Authenticator
    U->>G: Scan QR code or enter manual key
    G-->>U: Generate 6-digit TOTP code

    Note over U,K: 5. Confirm 2FA setup — POST /auth/2fa/confirm

    U->>F: Enter 6-digit code
    F->>A: POST /auth/2fa/confirm {code, setupToken}  Authorization: Bearer accessToken
    A->>A: requireAuth — jwt.verify(token) → {userId, email, role}
    A->>A: TwoFactorPolicy.validateCode(code) — /^\d{6}$/
    A->>A: TwoFactorPolicy.validateSetupToken(setupToken)
    A->>D: findById(userId)
    D-->>A: User found
    A->>C: GET auth:2fa:setup:{userId}:{setupToken}
    C-->>A: base32secret | null

    alt Setup session expired (TTL 300s)
        A-->>F: 400 {error: {code: SETUP_SESSION_EXPIRED}}
        F-->>U: Show expired session message
    else Secret found
        A->>A: speakeasy.totp.verify(base32secret, code, window=1)

        alt Code invalid
            A-->>F: 401 {error: {code: INVALID_2FA_CODE}}
            F-->>U: Show invalid code message
        else Code valid
            A->>D: UPDATE users SET twoFactorSecret=secret, isTwoFactorEnabled=true WHERE id=userId
            D-->>A: Updated
            A->>C: DELETE auth:2fa:setup:{userId}:{setupToken}
            C-->>A: Deleted
            A->>M: create {action:ENABLE_2FA_CONFIRM, status:SUCCESS, userId, email}
            A->>K: publish user.two_factor_enabled {userId, email, enabledAt}
            A-->>F: 200 {message: Two-factor authentication enabled successfully, isTwoFactorEnabled: true}
            F-->>U: 2FA enabled
        end
    end

    Note over U,G: 6. Get code from Google Authenticator
    U->>G: Open app
    G-->>U: Generate 6-digit TOTP code

    Note over U,K: 7. Verify 2FA login — POST /auth/login/2fa

    U->>F: Enter 6-digit code
    F->>A: POST /auth/login/2fa {email, challengeId, code}
    A->>A: TwoFactorPolicy.validateCode(code)
    A->>A: TwoFactorPolicy.validateChallengeId(challengeId)
    A->>C: GET auth:login:challenge:{challengeId}
    C-->>A: serializedChallenge | null

    alt Challenge expired (TTL 300s)
        A-->>F: 400 {error: {code: LOGIN_CHALLENGE_EXPIRED}}
        F-->>U: Show expired challenge message
    else Challenge found
        A->>A: JSON.parse(serializedChallenge) → challenge
        A->>A: Verify challenge.email === input.email

        alt Email mismatch
            A-->>F: 400 {error: {code: CHALLENGE_EMAIL_MISMATCH}}
            F-->>U: Show mismatch error
        else Email matches
            A->>D: findByEmail(email)
            D-->>A: User with twoFactorSecret
            A->>A: speakeasy.totp.verify(twoFactorSecret, code, window=1)

            alt Code invalid
                A-->>F: 401 {error: {code: INVALID_2FA_CODE}}
                F-->>U: Show invalid code message
            else Code valid
                A->>A: jwt.sign({userId, email, role}, JWT_ACCESS_SECRET, 15m) → accessToken
                A->>A: jwt.sign({userId, email, role}, JWT_REFRESH_SECRET, 7d) → refreshToken
                A->>C: DELETE auth:login:challenge:{challengeId}
                C-->>A: Deleted
                A->>M: create {action:VERIFY_LOGIN_2FA, status:SUCCESS, metadata:{viaTwoFactor:true, challengeId}}
                A->>K: publish user.logged_in {userId, email, loggedInAt, viaTwoFactor: true}
                A-->>F: 200 {accessToken} + Set-Cookie: refreshToken HttpOnly Secure SameSite=Strict
                F-->>U: Enter dashboard
            end
        end
    end

    Note over U,M: 8. Refresh access token — POST /auth/refresh

    U->>F: accessToken expired
    F->>A: POST /auth/refresh  Cookie: refreshToken=...
    A->>A: Read refreshToken from req.cookies.refreshToken

    alt Cookie missing
        A-->>F: 401 {error: {code: REFRESH_TOKEN_MISSING}}
        F-->>U: Redirect to login
    else Cookie present
        A->>A: jwt.verify(refreshToken, JWT_REFRESH_SECRET) → {userId, email, role}

        alt Invalid or expired refreshToken
            A-->>F: 401 {error: {code: INVALID_REFRESH_TOKEN}}
            F-->>U: Redirect to login
        else Valid refreshToken
            A->>D: findById(userId)
            D-->>A: User found
            A->>A: jwt.sign({userId, email, role}, JWT_ACCESS_SECRET, 15m) → accessToken
            A->>M: create {action:REFRESH_TOKEN, status:SUCCESS, userId, email}
            A-->>F: 200 {accessToken}
            F-->>U: Continue session
        end
    end

    Note over U,C: 9. Logout — POST /auth/logout

    U->>F: Click logout
    F->>A: POST /auth/logout  Authorization: Bearer accessToken
    A->>A: requireAuth — jwt.verify(accessToken) → {userId, email, role}
    A->>C: GET auth:blacklist:{accessToken}

    alt Token invalid or already blacklisted
        A-->>F: 401 Unauthorized
        F-->>U: Already logged out
    else Valid token
        A->>C: SET auth:blacklist:{accessToken} = 1  TTL:900s
        C-->>A: OK
        A->>M: create {action:LOGOUT, status:SUCCESS, userId, email}
        A-->>F: 200 {message: Logged out successfully} + Set-Cookie: refreshToken= Max-Age=0
        F-->>U: Redirect to login
    end

    Note over U,M: 10. Admin — GET /admin/audit-logs

    U->>F: Open admin dashboard
    F->>A: GET /admin/audit-logs?page=1&limit=20  Authorization: Bearer accessToken
    A->>A: requireAdmin — jwt.verify(accessToken) → payload

    alt Not authenticated
        A-->>F: 401 {error: {code: UNAUTHORIZED}}
        F-->>U: Redirect to login
    else role !== admin
        A-->>F: 403 {error: {message: Admin access required, code: FORBIDDEN}}
        F-->>U: Show forbidden error
    else Admin authenticated
        A->>M: findAll(filters, page, limit) — sort createdAt desc
        M-->>A: {data: AuditLog[], total, page, limit}
        A-->>F: 200 {items, total, page, limit}
        F-->>U: Display audit logs table
    end

    Note over U,C: 11. Admin — Debug endpoints

    U->>F: Open debug tools
    F->>A: GET /admin/debug/redis/health  Authorization: Bearer accessToken
    A->>C: SET + GET + DELETE admin:health:{timestamp}
    C-->>A: OK
    A-->>F: 200 {status: ok, connected: true|false}

    F->>A: GET /admin/debug/login-challenge/{challengeId}  Authorization: Bearer accessToken
    A->>C: GET 2fa:login:{challengeId}
    C-->>A: value | null
    A-->>F: 200 {type: LOGIN_CHALLENGE, key, exists, ttlSeconds}

    F->>A: GET /admin/debug/2fa-setup/{userId}/{token}  Authorization: Bearer accessToken
    A->>C: GET 2fa:setup:{userId}:{token}
    C-->>A: value | null
    A-->>F: 200 {type: TWO_FACTOR_SETUP, key, exists, ttlSeconds}